        <abstract>
            <p>Discusses Hildebrand</p>
            <p>and criticises Delpino.</p> 
<p>Asks to borrow C. K. Sprengel’s <hi rend="italic">Entdeckte Geheimniss der Natur</hi> [1793].</p>  
<p>Botanists have no explanation of the case of <hi rend="italic">Viola odorata</hi> and other showy flowers being sterile while inconspicuous ones bear seed.</p> 
        </abstract>
